In England, in the seven days to 30 September, there were 190,909 new confirmed cases (337.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 183,784 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (7,125 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 05 October is 6,780,567 (11,990.4 cases per 100,000 population).
